     I hadn't travelled far
  from Illinois in my 19 years

34
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:10,562
      I had been on Earth.

35
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:13,031
      And now here we were,
     brand new recruits from

36
00:02:13,099 --> 00:02:16,435
       all walks of life.

37
00:02:16,503 --> 00:02:18,504
         Willie McTear:
      Being from the South,

38
00:02:18,571 --> 00:02:20,305
        I was accustomed
        to two Americas,

39
00:02:20,373 --> 00:02:22,274
         a white America
      and a black America.

40
00:02:22,342 --> 00:02:25,010
      And this was being my
  first integration situation.

41
00:02:25,078 --> 00:02:27,012
           I was more
       nervous about that,

42
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,549
           than I was
       about the training.

43
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:35,154
          Larry Lilley:
     We all had a job to do,

44
00:02:35,221 --> 00:02:38,090
   so we worked well together.

45
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:41,126
        It was a blending
    that made us all better.

46
00:02:41,194 --> 00:02:44,997
      It didn't divide us,
       it made us better.

47
00:02:47,433 --> 00:02:49,501
          Steve Hopper:
     We met some crazy guys.

48
00:02:49,569 --> 00:02:52,437
        We had one of our
      guys, Terry McBride,

49
