   <i> individual replacements to</i>

83
00:04:35,158 --> 00:04:38,610
    <i> existing military units,</i>
   <i> Charlie Company is unique.</i>

84
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:41,346
    <i> One of the last American</i>
     <i> combat infantry units</i>

85
00:04:41,414 --> 00:04:45,817
     <i> to be drafted, trained</i>
   <i> and sent to war together.</i>

86
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:48,520
      Larry Lilley: We were
   told that we were going to

87
00:04:48,554 --> 00:04:52,257
    go to Vietnam as a group,
    right from the start and

88
00:04:52,325 --> 00:04:55,627
      pretty soon, through
  basic training, you realize,

89
00:04:55,695 --> 00:04:58,664
      "Oh that won't be bad
    I'll be with my buddies."

90
00:04:58,681 --> 00:05:00,899
       But still, Vietnam
    hung over our heads like

91
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:06,038
          a dark cloud.

92
