    pamphlets and things that
   dealt with our conscience,

175
00:10:26,325 --> 00:10:31,129
    because we were actually
  going to have to kill to keep

176
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:33,131
       from being killed.

177
00:10:33,199 --> 00:10:37,936
          That was just
       the reality of it.

178
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:46,077
    Gary Maibach: When we got
  closer to Vung Tau you could

179
00:10:46,128 --> 00:10:50,682
  see the coastline of Vietnam.

180
00:10:50,916 --> 00:10:53,685
        Shoreline with a
    beautiful beach, I mean,

181
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:56,354
       it looked more like
     somewhere you'd want to

182
00:10:56,422 --> 00:11:00,959
      take a vacation than
   you'd want to fight a war.

183
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:03,895
          Steve Hopper:
    We were out on the deck,

184
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:07,365
    just talking and looking,
    and you'd see a stream of

